This paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category as it presents a novel resource analysis for logic programs based on sized types, which are a type-based approach to program analysis. Additionally, the paper mentions that the analysis has been integrated into the Ciao preprocessor, which is a logic programming language. 

The paper also involves logic (cs.LO) as it deals with logic programs and predicates. 

Software Engineering (cs.SE) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the development of a new resource analysis within the abstract interpretation framework, which is a technique used in software engineering for program analysis. 

Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the formal analysis of logic programs using abstract domains. 

Finally, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the setting up and solving of recurrence equations, which are commonly used in the analysis of algorithms.
